Cardiovascular diseases and respiratory impairments in patients lead to difficulties in breathing and negative effects on their mental health. Clinical sleep analysis, a vital tool for early diagnosis and treatment, traditionally relies on expensive polysomnography systems. Recent advances in computer vision and machine learning have opened the door to more accessible and cost-effective alternatives. This paper introduces a novel convolutional neural network to estimate critical sleep parameters from RGB videos captured by a single-view camera. Empirical evaluations on a public dataset of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease patients indicate that the proposed framework surpasses current state-of-the-art approaches and shows significant improvements in predicting general sleep parameters (including sleep duration, sleep quality index, and oxygen saturation levels), while utilizing fewer parameters and alleviating the need for manual feature extraction.

Neurological disorders and motor impairments in patients lead to difficulties in movement and negative effects on their cognitive health. Clinical gait analysis, a vital tool for early diagnosis and treatment, traditionally relies on expensive motion capture systems. Recent advances in computer vision and machine learning have opened the door to more accessible and cost-effective alternatives. This paper introduces a novel recurrent neural network to estimate critical gait parameters from RGB videos captured by a single-view camera. Empirical evaluations on a public dataset of Parkinson's disease patients indicate that the proposed framework surpasses current state-of-the-art approaches and shows significant improvements in predicting general gait parameters (including stride length, cadence, and balance), while utilizing fewer parameters and alleviating the need for manual feature extraction.

Traditional approaches to culinary discovery, such as rigid recipe adherence and predetermined ingredient pairings, can be stifling and lacking in creativity. Recent advancements in food technology and online recipe platforms have opened up new avenues for more intuitive and personalized explorations. This paper presents a groundbreaking culinary framework that leverages data from user-generated recipes and real-time feedback to identify early warning signs of flavor fatigue, dish predictability, and culinary stagnation. Experimental results on a vast dataset of food blogs and online input reveal that the proposed model outperforms existing approaches in detecting subtle signs of innovation, while minimizing reliance on preconceived notions and personal biases.

The thrill of artistic expression has long been a quest for musicians to craft novel melodies that captivate the senses and evoke emotional resonance. Conventional approaches to musical discovery, such as rigid genre adherence and predetermined chord progressions, can be stifling and lacking in creativity. Recent advancements in audio technology and online music platforms have opened up new avenues for more intuitive and personalized explorations. This paper presents a groundbreaking musical framework that leverages data from user-generated playlists and real-time feedback to identify early warning signs of sonic fatigue, musical predictability, and artistic stagnation. Experimental results on a vast dataset of music blogs and online input reveal that the proposed model outperforms existing approaches in detecting subtle signs of innovation, while minimizing reliance on preconceived notions and personal biases.
